[normal]Legal aid should be removed for all cases assessed as having “borderline” prospects of success.[bold]Most  of the circumstances detailed below apply especially to  those of non-white /non-British origin, with in 
[normal]many cases women being foremost amongst them. They are almost without exception relegated to the lowest socio-economic rungs, and the recipients of societal discrimination  in employment, accommodation and treatment by statutory authorities  tasked with pu
[normal]blic order and border control. We fully  recognizing the need for  sensible border controls , serving our national interest of resource distribution and balanced economic development. Yet we find it extremely difficult to persuade ourselves that the measur
[normal]es proposed do serve these common purposes rather than amount to a generalised discrimination amounting to xenophobia.
[normal]We will now comment specifically on each of the above groups listed: 
